        "slug": "technical-barriers-for-local-cafes",
        "title": "Technical Barriers for Local Cafés",
        "excerpt": "Most local cafés depend on good products and friendly service to bring people back. However, many do not have an easy way to stay in touch with customers after they leave.",
        "content": "\n\n<h3>Technical Barriers for Local Cafés</h3>\n<p>Most local cafés depend on good products and friendly service to bring people back. However, many do not have an easy way to stay in touch with customers after they leave. Once someone walks out with their coffee, the relationship usually ends there.</p>\n\n<h3>Where Friction Exists Today</h3>\n<p>Local cafés often run into the same issues:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>No direct way to reach customers:</strong> After a purchase, cafés usually cannot contact customers again unless they walk back in on their own.</li>\n<li><strong>Manual or outdated loyalty programs:</strong> Paper punch cards are easy to lose, forget, or ignore.</li>\n<li><strong>Difficulty filling slow days:</strong> When business is slow, cafés have no quick way to tell customers about specials or promotions.</li>\n<li><strong>Little visibility into customer behavior:</strong> Owners cannot easily see who their regular customers are or which offers bring people back.</li>\n<li><strong>High cost of custom apps:</strong> Building a custom mobile app is expensive and unrealistic for most small cafés.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Why This Hurts Revenue</h3>\n<p>Because of these frictions, fewer customers return regularly and opportunities to increase repeat visits are missed. Cafés rely heavily on walk-in traffic and third-party platforms, with no clear way to improve loyalty over time. Even a small increase in repeat visits can make a noticeable difference in monthly revenue.</p>\n\n<h3>How Buildify Helps</h3>\n<p>Buildify helps cafés reduce these problems by giving them simple tools:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A branded mobile app that keeps the café connected with customers</li>\n<li>Digital rewards that encourage repeat visits</li>\n<li>Push notifications to promote new items or slow-day specials</li>\n<li>Event and update features to keep regulars engaged</li>\n<li>Insights that show what customers respond to and what they do not</li>\n</ul>\n<p>These tools are provided without the cost or complexity of building custom software.</p>\n\n<h3>Expected Outcome</h3>\n<p>With these friction points reduced, cafés can reasonably expect a 5 to 10 percent improvement in customer retention. More customers returning means more monthly revenue, which is what the ROI calculator is designed to show.</p>",
